column104: "Allowing" is a difficult word. But, to the extent that their preferred behaviors are unlikely to cause long-term, substantial harm to themselves or those around them, it seems like it is justifiable. After all, many enjoy drinking poison (i.e., alcohol) on a weekly basis and we generally accept that people have the right to make that choice for themselves.
